Declare this class somewhere, available for use in your unit tests
```
public class ReflectionMemberMatchingRule : IMemberMatchingRule
{
    public SelectedMemberInfo Match(SelectedMemberInfo expectedMember, object subject, string memberPath, IEquivalencyAssertionOptions config) =&gt; expectedMember;
}
```

Use the extension class in your unit tests, by adding the configuration to Fluent Assertions.
```
AssertionOptions.AssertEquivalencyUsing(x =&gt; x.Using(new ReflectionMemberMatchingRule()));
```

It now works as expected!

